00:47:12.210 --> 00:47:15.470
Suppose you're trying to
understand what this does as x

00:47:15.470 --> 00:47:18.200
goes to infinity.

00:47:18.200 --> 00:47:23.770
Now, you could L'Hopital's
Rule five

00:47:23.770 --> 00:47:25.700
times, or four times.

00:47:25.700 --> 00:47:30.040
And get the answer here.

00:47:30.040 --> 00:47:33.260
But really, you should realize
that the main terms are

00:47:33.260 --> 00:47:34.870
sitting there right
in front of you.

00:47:34.870 --> 00:47:36.470
And that there's some
algebra that you can

00:47:36.470 --> 00:47:38.490
do to simplify this.

00:47:38.490 --> 00:47:45.450
Namely, it's the same as
1 + 2 / x + 1 / x^ 5.

00:47:48.060 --> 00:47:51.510
And then in the denominator,
well, let's see.

00:47:51.510 --> 00:47:53.110
It's x.

00:47:53.110 --> 00:47:57.965
So this would be dividing by 1
/ x^ 5 in both numerator and

00:47:57.965 --> 00:47:58.240
denominator.

00:47:58.240 --> 00:48:04.410
And here you have 1 / x + 2
over, sorry I overshot.

00:48:04.410 --> 00:48:06.250
But that's OK.

00:48:06.250 --> 00:48:09.110
2 / x^ 5 here.

00:48:09.110 --> 00:48:12.650
So these are the main
term, if you like.

00:48:12.650 --> 00:48:18.590
And it's the same as 1 / 1 / x,
which is the same as x, and

00:48:18.590 --> 00:48:21.490
it goes to infinity.

00:48:21.490 --> 00:48:22.930
As x goes to infinity.

00:48:22.930 --> 00:48:28.040
Or, if you like, much more
simply, just x ^ 5 / x^ 4 is

00:48:28.040 --> 00:48:29.230
the main term.

00:48:29.230 --> 00:48:30.520
Which is x.

00:48:30.520 --> 00:48:31.590
Which goes to infinity.

00:48:31.590 --> 00:48:36.110
So don't forget your basic
algebra when you're doing this

00:48:36.110 --> 00:48:37.210
kind of stuff.

00:48:37.210 --> 00:48:40.640
Use these things and don't
use L'Hopital's Rule.

